Relation Between Average Total Delayed Arrival Time (min) And Year¶

In [34]:
df_year = df.groupby('year')['total_arr_delay_min'].mean().reset_index()
plt.figure(figsize = [8, 5])
base_color = sb.color_palette()[0]
sb.lineplot(data = df_year, x='year', y='total_arr_delay_min', color = base_color)
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Average Total Delayed Arrival Time (min)")
plt.title("Relation Between Average Total Delayed Arrival Time (min) And Year");

The Figure shows the variation in the average total delayed time in minutes per each year. And it shows that 2016 has the most delayed time which is more than 5000 minutes. And 2020 has the least delayed time which is around 1500 minutes.

sb.lineplot(data = df_reasons, x='year', y='security_count', label = "Security Delayed Flights")

df_reasons = df.groupby('year')['late_aircraft_count'].sum().reset_index()

df_reasons = df.groupby('year')['arr_cancelled_count'].sum().reset_index()
sb.lineplot(data = df_reasons, x='year', y='arr_cancelled_count', label = "Cancelled Flights")

plt.xlabel('Year', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Count', fontsize=14);

The prevoius figure shows the variation of the delay reasons over the years. It shows that the least delay was because of security issue, and the most delay was because of late aircraft issue. We can notice that the most number of cancelled flights was in 2020 and we can conclude that it was because of the covid 19 pandemic.

Percentage of Number Of Flights Delayed Of Each Reason Type¶

In [42]:
total_no_of_flights = df.arr_flights_on_time.sum() + df.carrier_count.sum() + df.weather_count.sum() + df.nas_count.sum() + df.security_count.sum() + df.late_aircraft_count.sum() + df.arr_cancelled_count.sum() + df.arr_diverted_count.sum()
perc_on_time = (df.arr_flights_on_time.sum() / total_no_of_flights) * 100
perc_carrier = (df.carrier_count.sum() / total_no_of_flights) * 100
perc_weather = (df.weather_count.sum() / total_no_of_flights) * 100
perc_nas = (df.nas_count.sum() / total_no_of_flights) * 100
perc_security = (df.security_count.sum() / total_no_of_flights) * 100
perc_late_aircraft = (df.late_aircraft_count.sum() / total_no_of_flights) * 100
perc_cancelled = (df.arr_cancelled_count.sum() / total_no_of_flights) * 100
perc_diverted = (df.arr_diverted_count.sum() / total_no_of_flights) * 100
#print(perc_on_time, perc_carrier, perc_weather, perc_nas, perc_security, perc_late_aircraft, perc_cancelled, perc_diverted)

plt.figure(figsize = [10, 10])
labels = 'On Time : 82.7%', 'Carrier Delay : 4.4%', 'Weather Delay : 0.5%', 'National Aviation System Delay : 5.2%', 'Security Delay : 0.0%', 'Late Aircraft Delay : 5.4%', 'Cancelled Flights : 1.6%', 'Diverted Flights : 0.2%'
sizes = [perc_on_time, perc_carrier, perc_weather, perc_nas, perc_security, perc_late_aircraft, perc_cancelled, perc_diverted]

plt.pie(sizes, startangle=90)
plt.axis('equal') 
plt.legend(labels)
plt.title('Percentage of Number Of Flights Delayed Of Each Type', fontsize=16)
plt.show();

We can see from the pie chart the percent of the number of flights arrived on time and the flights delayed. And it actually approves with the previous line chart which shows that the least number of flights delayed because of security issue, and the most number of flights delayed because of late aircraft.
